\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Confusion matrix for the v3 hierarchical CNN model on binary classification (DNA vs non-DNA). Cell intensity represents classification frequency; diagonal elements (correct predictions) dominate. The small off-diagonal mass is concentrated at the boundary between DNA and non-DNA, indicating that classification errors arise from sequences close to the decision boundary rather than being randomly distributed across classes.}}{16}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:v3_confusion}{{3}{16}{Confusion matrix for the v3 hierarchical CNN model on binary classification (DNA vs non-DNA). Cell intensity represents classification frequency; diagonal elements (correct predictions) dominate. The small off-diagonal mass is concentrated at the boundary between DNA and non-DNA, indicating that classification errors arise from sequences close to the decision boundary rather than being randomly distributed across classes}{figure.3}{}}
