\newlabel{fig:v4_confusion}{{4}{17}{Confusion matrices for the v4 hybrid CNN+GNN model: binary DNA vs non-DNA (left) and DNA-superfamily classification across seven families (right). The hybrid architecture shows modest gains over v3, mainly for the binary task, where the GNN's compositional signal provides additional separability; superfamily performance is comparable to v3}{figure.4}{}}
