\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces K-mer feature separability for top-level classes, showing that 7-mer frequency composition alone achieves ~85\% macro F1 on class discrimination (DNA/LTR/LINE). This analysis justifies the GNN component of the hybrid architecture: compositional signals provide strong priors for class identity, reducing the hypothesis space for CNN-driven fine-grained superfamily classification.}}{21}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:kmer_separation}{{7}{21}{K-mer feature separability for top-level classes, showing that 7-mer frequency composition alone achieves ~85\% macro F1 on class discrimination (DNA/LTR/LINE). This analysis justifies the GNN component of the hybrid architecture: compositional signals provide strong priors for class identity, reducing the hypothesis space for CNN-driven fine-grained superfamily classification}{figure.7}{}}
